    "source": "mcgee.pdf_page_469",
    "contenu": "Here is the structured content extracted from the provided document titled \"SEEDS AND HEALTH\":\n\n---\n\n### VALUABLE PHYTOCHEMICALS FROM SEEDS\n\nTowards the end of the 20th century, it was recognized that seeds have more to offer than just the basic life machinery. Epidemiological studies discovered that a general consumption of whole grains, legumes, nuts, and seeds reduces various cancers, heart disease, and diabetes. Foods derived from these seeds hold thousands of chemicals that are primarily found in their outer protective layers. These beneficial chemicals include:\n- A variety of **vitamins**, such as vitamin E and tocotrienols\n- **Soluble fiber**: helps slow digestion, moderate blood insulin and sugar levels, and reduces cholesterol. It provides energy, enhances the intestinal flora, suppresses harmful bacteria, and improves intestinal cell health.\n- **Insoluble fiber**: aids in speeding the passage of food through the digestive system.\n- A variety of **phenolic and other defensive compounds** that act as antioxidants, inhibit carcinogens, mimic hormones, and may help prevent cancer.\n\n### PROBLEMS CAUSED BY SEEDS\n\nWhile seeds offer numerous health benefits, they are not without issues:\n1. **Defensive Chemicals**: Legumes contain lectins and protease inhibitors that can lead to malnutrition and other problems despite cooking, which does not deactivate these chemicals.\n2. **Allergies**: Seeds can cause severe allergic reactions in people due to their immune system misidentifying seed proteins as threats. Common allergens include peanuts, soybeans, and tree nuts. Approximately 2% of adults and 8% of children in the U.S. are affected, with the potential for life-threatening reactions.\n3. **Gluten Sensitivity**: Another issue is an autoimmune disorder caused by gluten found in wheat, barley, rye, etc., where the body negatively reacts to gliadin proteins.\n\nMedical scientists are actively studying and evaluating the array of phytochemicals in seeds to better understand and leverage their health benefits.\n\n--- \n\nThis content highlights both the beneficial and problematic aspects related to the consumption of seeds and their health impacts as outlined in the document."
  },
