    "contenu": "The provided document contains two recipes, each presented with associated tips and instructions. Here's the content structured for readability:\n\n---\n\n### Préparer du houmous\n\n**Description:**\nThis recipe is for a basic hummus, often enjoyed as an appetizer, in sandwiches, or with fresh vegetables. It includes chickpeas, olive oil, and yogurt as key ingredients.\n\n**Ingrédients:**\n- 400 g de pois chiches déjà cuits\n- 2 gousses d'ail\n- 3 cuillères à soupe de tahini (purée de sésame)\n- 1 citron\n- 2 à 4 cl d'eau ou de liquide de cuisson des pois chiches, selon la texture désirée\n- 1 cuillère à café de sel fin\n- 2 à 3 cuillères à soupe d'huile d'olive\n\n**Préparation:** \n1. Peel and degrease the garlic, then blend it with the cooked chickpeas, tahini, juice of one lemon, salt, and water. Mix until achieving a creamy consistency, adding a little water if necessary.\n2. Add olive oil, mix well and serve.\n\n**Chef's advice:**\nIf using canned chickpeas, save the preservation liquid to adjust the hummus texture by possibly adding it to the blend after rinsing and drying the chickpeas.\n\n**Good to know:**\n- The hummus can be stored for 5 days in an airtight container.\n- It can be enjoyed with pita bread, cucumbers, or decorated with paprika.\n\n### Réhydrater des vermicelles de haricots mungo\n\n**Description:**\nThis recipe focuses on preparing and utilizing mung bean noodles, known for their essential role in East Asian cuisines and often mislabeled in packaging.\n\n**Ingrédients:**\n- 100 g de nouilles de haricots mungo\n- 1 litre d'eau bouillante\n\n**Préparation:** \n1. Pour boiling water over the noodles. Let them swell for 15 minutes, then drain and cut with scissors.\n2. The prepared noodles can be used in spring rolls, with nems, or simply sautéd with vegetables.\n\n**Good to know:**\n- Once rehydrated, the noodles can be stored for up to 3 days in an airtight container in the refrigerator.\n\n**Recommended recipe tip:** \n- Spring rolls at page 315 of the book.\n\n---\n\nThis format provides a clear structure, listing both ingredients and preparation steps for each recipe which enables easy understanding and application of the instructions from the document."
